{{Infobox event | title = Encounter killing of Naqeebullah Mehsud | image = | image_size = <!-- |image_upright= is preferred for most cases, see WP:IMGSIZE --> | image_upright = | image_alt = | caption = | native_name = {{nq|نقيب الله محسود}} | native_name_lang = ps | english_name = | time = | duration = | date = {{start date|2018|01|13}} | venue = | location = | coordinates = <!-- {{coord|LAT|LON|region:XXXX_type:event|display=inline,title}} --> | also_known_as = | type = | theme = | cause = | motive = | target = | first_reporter = | budget = | patron = <!-- or |patrons= --> | organisers = <!-- or |organizers= --> | filmed_by = | participants = | outcome = | casualties1 = | casualties2 = | casualties3 = | reported deaths = 4 | reported injuries = | reported missing = | reported property damage = | burial = | inquiries = | inquest = | coroner = | arrests = | suspects = | accused = | convicted = | charges = | trial = | verdict = | convictions = | sentence = | publication_bans = | litigation = | awards = | url = | blank_label = <!-- or |blank_data= --> | blank1_label = <!-- or |blank1_data= --> | blank2_label = <!-- or |blank2_data= --> | website = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} --> | notes = }}
The '''encounter killing of Naqeebullah Mehsud''' occurred on 13 January 2018, in the eastern suburbs of [[Karachi]], following the [[Police encounter|encounter]] carried out by Rao Anwar.<ref name="aj">{{cite web|url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2018/03/manzoor-pashteen-voice-pashtuns-pakistan-180314091327342.html|title=Manzoor Pashteen: The voice of Pashtuns for many in Pakistan|website=www.aljazeera.com}}</ref><ref name="aljazeera1">{{Cite news |url=http://www.aljazeera.com/news/2018/01/police-killing-naqeebullah-mehsud-angers-pakistanis-180119081758397.html |title=Police killing of Naqeebullah Mehsud angers Pakistanis |last=Hashim |first=Asad |date=2018-01-19 |access-date=2018-01-23 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180120221955/http://www.aljazeera.com/news/2018/01/police-killing-naqeebullah-mehsud-angers-pakistanis-180119081758397.html |archivedate=2018-01-20 |df= }}</ref> Mehsud was charged with [[Militant|militancy]] and links with [[Lashkar-e-Jhangvi]] and the [[Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant]].<ref name="dawn1">{{Cite news |url=https://www.dawn.com/news/1382684 |title=4 militants linked with high-profile terror cases killed in Karachi police 'encounter' |last=Ali |first=Imtiaz |date=2018-01-13 |work=DAWN.COM |access-date=2018-01-23 |language=en-US |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180120063451/https://www.dawn.com/news/1382684 |archivedate=2018-01-20 |df= }}</ref> The claim was contested by the relatives and subsequently an inquiry team was formed to investigate the killing.<ref name="dawn2">{{Cite news |url=https://www.dawn.com/news/1383540/anger-on-social-media-after-waziristan-man-killed-in-karachi-encounter |title=Anger on social media after Waziristan man killed in Karachi 'encounter' |last=Ali |first=Imtiaz |date=2018-01-18 |work=DAWN.COM |access-date=2018-01-23 |language=en-US |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180122063616/https://www.dawn.com/news/1383540/anger-on-social-media-after-waziristan-man-killed-in-karachi-encounter |archivedate=2018-01-22 |df= }}</ref><ref name="geo.tv">{{Cite news |url=https://www.geo.tv/latest/177441-bilawal-orders-inquiry-into-south-waziristan-youths-killing |title=IGP forms committee to probe killing of Waziristan man in Karachi 'police shootout' |last=Mushtaq |first=Kashif |date=2018-01-18 |access-date=2018-01-23 |language=en-US |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180118082128/https://www.geo.tv/latest/177441-bilawal-orders-inquiry-into-south-waziristan-youths-killing |archivedate=2018-01-18 |df= }}</ref> The investigation found that Mehsud was innocent, and that before his murder, he was forcefully abducted during a raid by police personnel on the evening of 3 January 2018 in Karachi. He went missing for 10 days and was then killed in a fake encounter.<ref name="aj"/><ref name="dawn3">{{Cite news |url=https://www.dawn.com/news/1384163 |title=Naqeebullah was killed in ‘fake encounter’, had no militant tendencies: police inquiry finds |last=Ali |first=Imtiaz |date=2018-01-20 |work=DAWN.COM |access-date=2018-01-23 |language=en-US |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180123055606/https://www.dawn.com/news/1384163 |archivedate=2018-01-23 |df= }}</ref>
